beer.beer_description:
Phat Mongrel’s older, inappropriate uncle. Bigger bodied, more bitter, with extra mongrel.

To the eye: Black and viscous like sump oil, the nitro charge gives the appearance of a blown head gasket.
Up your nose: Bangs of dark roasted malt goodness. Coffee, cacao and slightly burnt. Rounded out with the early fruit spice.

In your mouth: Voluptuously full bodied. Mouth coasting sweetness balanced with 100 IBU’s and a boozy warming sensation.
